{"questionId":"27904","questionHtml":"<div class=\"qb-parent-stem\"><p>A particle moves such that its velocity, <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>v</mi></math> metres per second, at time <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>t</mi></math> seconds,&nbsp;is given by <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>v</mi><mo>=</mo><mi>t</mi><mo> </mo><mi>sin</mi><mo>(</mo><msup><mi>t</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>)</mo></math>.</p></div>\n<div class=\"qb-parent-stem\"><p>The particle starts at the origin.</p></div>\n<div class=\"qb-leaf-prompt\"><p>Hence show that the particle never has a negative displacement.</p></div>","markschemeHtml":"<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>cos</mi><mfenced><msup><mi>t</mi><mn>2</mn></msup></mfenced><mo>≤</mo><mn>1</mn></math>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;<em><strong>A1</strong></em></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>-</mo><mfrac><mn>1</mn><mn>2</mn></mfrac><mi>cos</mi><mfenced><msup><mi>t</mi><mn>2</mn></msup></mfenced><mo>≥</mo><mo>-</mo><mfrac><mn>1</mn><mn>2</mn></mfrac></math></p>\n<p>so&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfrac><mn>1</mn><mn>2</mn></mfrac><mo>-</mo><mfrac><mn>1</mn><mn>2</mn></mfrac><mi>cos</mi><mfenced><msup><mi>t</mi><mn>2</mn></msup></mfenced><mo>≥</mo><mn>0</mn></math>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;<em><strong>R1</strong></em></p>\n<p>hence the particle never has a negative displacement.&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;<em><strong>AG</strong></em></p>\n<p><br><strong>Note:</strong> Do not accept reasoning based on a sketch of the graph.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><em><strong>[2 marks]</strong></em></p>","meta":{"questionId":"27904","referenceCode":"22N.1.AHL.TZ0.14d","subjectId":"51-dp-mathematics-applications-and-interpretation","title":"Hence show that the particle never has a negative displacement.","paper":"1","level":"HL","questionNumber":"d","marksAvailable":"[Maximum mark: 2]","breadcrumbLabels":["Topic 5—Calculus","Topic 5—Calculus","AHL 5.11—Indefinite integration, reverse chain, by substitution","Topic 5—Calculus","AHL 5.13—Kinematic problems"],"memberSectionIds":[],"sectionOrders":{}},"schemaVersion":2}